						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vijayanagar. Dēvarāya, Śaka 1365, Rudhirotkāri = 1443 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Much damaged. Seems to record a gift, by Prince Vijayarāyar, of land as dēvadāna to the temple at Talaivānallūr, which was a hamlet of the brahamadēyam-Taṉiyūr Rājarāja-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Paṉaiyūr-nāḍu. The gift was meant to be an endowment for supply of flowers to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
